step.tex:
\vert x-2\vert = \begin{cases}
x-2, x\geq 2 \\
2-x, x\lt 2
\end{cases}\\

\vert x-4\vert = \begin{cases}
x-4, x\geq 4 \\
4-x, x\lt 4
\end{cases}

\vert x-2\vert = \begin{cases}
x-2, x\geq 0 \\
2-x, x\lt 0
\end{cases}\\

\vert x-4\vert = \begin{cases}
x-4, x\geq 0 \\
4-x, x\lt 0
\end{cases}

step.reason:
%text Here is how you should think about $\vert x-a\vert$. If $x-a = z, (a\gt 0)$, then $\vert x-a\vert = \vert z\vert$. Now, we know that % \vert z\vert = \begin{cases} z\text{ if } z\geq 0 \\ -z\text{ if } z\lt 0 \end{cases} %text
But as $z=x-a$, thererfore % \vert z\vert = \vert x-a\vert = \begin{cases} x-a\text{ if } x-a\geq 0 \implies x\geq a \\ a-x\text{ if }x-a\lt 0\implies x\lt a \end{cases} \\ \text{Which is why } \vert x-2\vert = \begin{cases} x-2, x\geq 2 \\ 2-x, x\lt 2 \end{cases}\text{ and } \\
\vert x-4\vert = \begin{cases} x-4, x\geq 4 \\ 4-x, x\lt 4 \end{cases}
